          "id": "music-history-101-l14-c2",
          "title": "Connections to Today",
          "content": "It's fascinating to see how every modern music genre is connected to the past! For instance, the way melodies are structured in pop music can be traced back to the symmetry found in classical music phrases. If you listen to rock music, you might notice that the guitar solos often reflect the virtuosity that was celebrated during the Romantic period. Jazz music, with its focus on improvisation, has roots in the elaborate ornamentation used in Baroque music. Even hip-hop, which is known for its sampling, draws from a long tradition of composers who quoted each other throughout history. When you hear film scores, you can recognize influences from the orchestral writing of the Late Romantic era. Additionally, the electronic sounds found in EDM (Electronic Dance Music) are inspired by the experimental approaches of 20th-century avant-garde musicians. By learning about music history, we can better understand these exciting connections and appreciate how they shape the music we enjoy today.\nContext recap: It's fascinating to see how every modern music genre is connected to the past! For instance, the way melodies are structured in pop music can be traced back to the symmetry found in classical music phrases. If you listen to rock music, you might notice that the guitar solos often reflect the virtuosity that was celebrated during the Romantic period. Jazz music, with its focus on improvisation, has roots in the elaborate ornamentation used in Baroque music.\nWhy this matters: Connections to Today helps learners in Music connect ideas from Music History: Medieval to Modern to decisions they make during practice and assessment. Connect ideas to real decisions and evidence."
